  "common": {
    "name": {
      "zh": "贝雷塔92FS 9x19手枪",
      "en": "Beretta 92FS 9x19 pistol"
    },
    "shortName": {
      "zh": "92FS",
      "en": "92FS"
    },
    "description": {
      "zh": "贝雷塔92FS（军用型号为M9）是1985年美国武装部队正式采用的制式手枪。20世纪80年代，92FS在一场竞标中胜出，取代M1911A1成为美军主力副武器，击败众多竞争对手后仅因成本因素险胜西格绍尔P226。该枪采用短后坐半自动原理，单/双动击发模式，配用15发双排弹匣。",
      "en": "The Beretta 92FS (military designation of M9), was the official service pistol adopted by the United States Armed Forces in 1985. The 92FS won a competition in the 1980s to replace the M1911A1 as the primary sidearm of the U.S. military, beating many other contenders and only narrowly defeating the SIG Sauer P226 for cost reasons. The weapon operates as a short recoil, semi-automatic, single-action/double-action pistol that uses a 15-round staggered box magazine."
    },
